Author::::Kaitain
DateTime::::2016-03-08T19:57:03Z
It took companies about a decade to realize that "cheats" (especially infinite lives) should really be a part of the game. I suspect that in the early days games developers felt:a) They should follow the amusement arcade model, which entailed a game lasting around ten minsb) If they made a game too easy it would be completed too quickly, and the customer might feel ripped off



Author::::Kaitain
DateTime::::2016-03-08T19:54:34Z
Shocking fact, once urban myth but verified:Ultimate created "Knight Lore" before they created "Sabre Wulf" (the development periods for both overlapped). However, they felt that once they'd released Knight Lore, Sabre Wulf would feel like old hat. So they sat on Knight Lore, released Sabre Wulf, made a boatload of cash from it then released Knight Lore later in the year.



